annotations: So be my bread and body

In the Bible, bread became the body of Christ during the Last Supper. When Jesus says, “I am the bread of life,” He is saying that He can satisfy our deepest needs and longings, which is what the girl would be doing for the singer by being their bread and body.
I’ll let you, I’ll be your man
Potentially a nod to Claire Altendahl’s use of they/them pronouns.

description.plain:
India Shore (she/they) and Claire Altendahl (they/them) both identify as gender non-conforming/nonbinary and queer. “AnDroGay” is a song about navigating a relationship with respect to those intersecting identities.
The singer’s love interest seems to reciprocate romantic feelings towards them but is reluctant to act on them on account of not wanting to be seen as gay, considering the love interest views the singer, who is nonbinary, as female.

description.plain:
I think this song is about once having a friend/lover that you had a strong friendship/relationship with and really cared about each other and loved each other but then ended up parting ways (there could be lots of different reasons for this) and now it’s not the same as it was. The singer feels like it was their fault and is feeling bad about their friendship/relationship falling apart ‘Congratulations
You fucked it all and now you’re alone’. The song is about the singer reflecting on the person they feel they have lost and remembering the good times they had with this person. The singer also seems to feel bitter about this person now which contrasts to how they used to feel about them which shows that everything has changed between them both ‘Remember when I cared for you, Sometimes I think I still do’. The singer has clearly changed how they feel about this person because of things the person may have said/done.
The singer also wishes that things could be the same between them as they used to be ‘I wanna tell you I’m scared
I think you know it’ The singer is remembering how they used to beable to be honest and open with this person about how they are feeling and wish they were still as close because they miss being able to do this with this person.
~This is just my interpretation of the song, It might not be exactly what the songwriter meant to say.
